  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save Lives through the Rehabilitation of Livelihoods for the Populations of the Hodh Ech Chargui Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the year of drought in Mauritania in 2019, this project is focusing on raising the livestock sector largely affected by the rainfall deficit and the poor distribution of plant cover, as well as better access to drinking water for fight against malnutrition and allow 200 women from host populations and refugees outside camps to carry out market gardening activities (supply of seeds, fencing, horticultural equipment, etc.). To this end, the target populations are 7,000 refugees from the Mb&#xE9;ra camp as well as 45,000 individuals (including host populations and refugees outside the camp), for a total of 52,000 direct beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
